There are several ways to duplicate a line on a Mac. 

1. Press Command + D to quickly duplicate the line you are currently on. 
2. Select the line you want to duplicate and press Option + Return to create a copy of the line below it. 
3. Highlight the line you want to duplicate, then right-click and select “Duplicate” from the menu. 
4. Use the Edit > Duplicate Line command in your text editor.